Title: Series: Theatrum Artis Pictoriae
Description: The flight into Egypt with at the centre of a landscape the Virgin and child on a donkey guided by St Joseph; nearby, two sleeping putti; after Domenico Fetti. 1728 Etching and engraving, with border and image printed from two separate plates
Producer name: Print made by: Anton Joseph Prenner
Curator's comments: For comment on the series see 1850,1021.84.+. After the painting in the Kunsthistorisches Museum (inv. GG_155). Also see Safarik, 1990, cat. No.16.
